==2015==
The second edition of Shamkir Chess took place 16-25 April 2015.

World champion [[Magnus Carlsen]], former world champion [[Viswanathan Anand]] and [[Vladimir Kramnik]] competed in the tournament in Azerbaijan, as well as [[Fabiano Caruana]], [[Anish Giri]], [[Wesley So]], [[Maxime Vachier-Lagrave]], [[Shakhriyar Mamedyarov]], [[Michael Adams (chess player)|Michael Adams]], and the Azerbaijan Champion [[Rauf Mamedov]].   

The tournament’s total prize fund was €100,000.

Magnus Carlsen won the event with 7 points out of 9

